    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix function signature mismatch in new_textlog() logger implementation\n\n### Summary\nThe NR tracer logging module contained a function signature mismatch between the declaration and implementation of new_textlog(). The header file declared the first parameter as void *event_handler while the implementation used event_handler *h directly.\n\nThis inconsistency caused unexpected behavior when calling new_textlog() from various tracer components, particularly in high-frequency logging scenarios where the parameter passing could result in incorrect handler registration.\n\nThe mismatch was introduced during a previous interface refactoring that changed parameter naming conventions but did not maintain consistency between declaration and definition.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/T/tracer/logger/textlog.c`: Updated function signature to match header declaration and added proper casting for internal usage.\n\n"
}